#![allow(unknown_attribute)]
# HAL — Generic Hardware Abstraction Layer
#
# Architecture-generic HAL functions that delegate to arch-specific
# implementations via @cfg conditional compilation.
#
# x86_64: fully implemented, delegates to x86_64/ submodules.
# arm64: Phase A+B+C implemented (console, cpu, boot, paging, interrupts, timer, context switch).
# riscv64: Phase A+B+C implemented (console, cpu, boot, paging, interrupts, timer, context switch).
# arm32: Phase A+B+C implemented (console, cpu, boot, paging, interrupts, timer, context switch).
# riscv32: Phase A+B+C implemented (console, cpu, boot, paging, interrupts, timer, context switch).
#
# Compile-time arch selection: @cfg(x86_64), @cfg(arm64), etc.
# Only the active arch's function body is compiled into the final binary.

